  "text": "3.3.2. 13 C CP MAS NMR Spectroscopy [CITATION_1] C CP MAS NMR measurement was carried out on a DSX spectrometer (Bruker, Karlsruhe, Germany). For the determination of NMR spectra, a sample of about 100 mg was placed in a ZrO 2 rotator with diameter 4 mm, which enabled spinning of the sample. Centrifugation at the magic angle was performed at a spinning frequency of 8 kHz. The 13 C CP MAS NMR spectra were recorded at 100.63 MHz in a standard 4 mm MAS probe using a single pulse excitation with high power proton decoupling (pulse repetition 10 s, spinning speed 8 kHz).",
